    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;section-divider&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;bio&#34;&gt;Bio&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I am a PhD Candidate in &lt;strong&gt;Blockchain and Distributed Ledger Technologies&lt;/strong&gt; within the &lt;a href=&#34;https://isas.unicam.it/dni/blockchain-and-DLT&#34;&gt;National PhD Program ISAS&lt;/a&gt; (University of Turin – University of Camerino). My research is carried out jointly at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.di.unito.it/do/home.pl&#34;&gt;Department of Computer Science, University of Turin&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=&#34;https://linksfoundation.com/en/&#34;&gt;Links Foundation&lt;/a&gt; in Torino, Italy.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My work sits at the intersection of &lt;strong&gt;distributed systems&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;applied cryptography&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;software engineering&lt;/strong&gt;. I focus on designing blockchain-based data marketplaces (with emphasis on the energy domain), investigating DAO governance sustainability through on-chain metrics, and exploring privacy-preserving techniques such as Zero-Knowledge proofs, Multi-Party Computation, and Fully Homomorphic Encryption.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
